<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-03-03T13:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-03-01T19:00:00-05:00" n="178" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d178">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 841.857/388</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Southampton</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Swalm</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Southampton</hi></placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1917-03-03T13:30:00-05:00" notBefore="1917-03-02T00:00:00+00:00"><hi rend="italic">undated</hi></date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received
                                    March 3, 1917, 1.30 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>British steamship <hi rend="italic">Belgier</hi> torpedoed February 23,
                            forty miles off Lauriat [<hi rend="italic">Lorient?</hi>], France, four
                            Americans in crew. Joint affidavit of <persName>Isadore
                            Frank</persName>, <persName>Leroy Kraig</persName>, <persName>DeWitt
                                Shivers</persName>, and <persName>Daniel Gatliff</persName>
                            forwarded. Bound New York to French port, cargo munitions. Vessel
                            stopped by gunfire, German submarine. Weather fine, French scout
                            appeared immediately, took crew from boats, landed at Lauriat [<hi rend="italic">Lorient?</hi>], sent here, no casualties, did not
                            resist.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Swalm</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>